b"@CrownHeightsMOV Colin Warner was a victim of this era and sacrificed 20 yrs of his life behind bars for a crime that he didn't commit. He was from Brooklyn."
b'@CrownHeightsMOV The "tough on crime" era began with terrible racist policies that led to horrible policing that destroyed the fabric of the black community.'
b"@CrownHeightsMOV We all knew a guy who got railroaded by the system. Everyone in the hood knew he didn't do it, but the cops and the DA got a conviction."
b'@CrownHeightsMOV In Hollis, almost every one I grew up either got sent away on some drug charge for decades or ended up dead. But we all knew a Colin Warner.'
b'@CrownHeightsMOV For far too many of us, who grew up in black and brown communities, we all know a Colin Warner. Someone who got locked up for far too long.'
b'@CrownHeightsMOV A criminal justice system deeply rooted in institutional racism, archaic sentencing laws + a war on drugs that decimated black communities.'
